    <meta name=3D"viewport" content=3D"width=3Ddevice-width, initial-scale=
=3D1">

    <title>Flag Semaphore Signaller</title>

    <meta name=3D"description" content=3D"Animated flag semaphore signaller=
">

   =20

   =20

   =20

</head>

<body>

    <h1>Animated Flag Semaphore Signaller</h1>

    <p class=3D"rubrik">Input your text into the box and the little man wil=
l signal your message in flag semaphore. Note that you do not have to use t=
he special "letters" and "numerals" signals before such runs of characters =
as the software will insert these automatically for you. Likewise, you also=
 don't need to input a move through rest (both flags down) before a repeate=
d character.<br>Before the man starts signalling (and at the end), he will =
signal "attention" (flags moved up and down).<br>See the end of this page f=
or further usage notes. Please see Wikipedia for a chart of all the flag co=
des.</p>

    <div id=3D"allcont"><img id=3D"man" src=3D"https://steve-p.org/sem/man.=
png" alt=3D""><img id=3D"normflagright" class=3D"flags flagsright" src=3D"h=
ttps://steve-p.org/sem/flagrightO.png" alt=3D""><img id=3D"crossflagright" =
class=3D"flags flagsright" src=3D"https://steve-p.org/sem/flagleftO.png" al=
t=3D""><img id=3D"normflagleft" class=3D"flags flagsleft" src=3D"https://st=
eve-p.org/sem/flagleftO.png" alt=3D""><img id=3D"crossflagleft" class=3D"fl=
ags flagsleft" src=3D"https://steve-p.org/sem/flagrightO.png" alt=3D""></di=
v>

    <form autocomplete=3D"off">

        <fieldset>
            <legend>Text to signal (150 characters max.)</legend>
            <textarea id=3D"astringinp" rows=3D"4" maxlength=3D"150"></text=
area><br>
            <button type=3D"button">Start Sequence</button>
            <button type=3D"button">Stop</button>
        </fieldset>

    </form>

    <form autocomplete=3D"off">

        <fieldset>
            <legend>Flag pause time (secs)</legend>
            <label class=3D"slider"><span class=3D"sliderrange">0.1</span><=
input id=3D"pauseleninp" type=3D"range" min=3D"0.1" max=3D"5" step=3D"0.1" =
value=3D"1"><span class=3D"sliderrange">5</span><span id=3D"pauseleninplab"=
 class=3D"inplab">1s</span></label>
        </fieldset>

    </form>

    <form autocomplete=3D"off">

        <fieldset>
            <legend>Flag movement speed</legend>
            <label class=3D"radio"><input type=3D"radio" name=3D"flagspeed"=
 value=3D"slow">slow</label>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<label class=3D"radio"><input=
 type=3D"radio" name=3D"flagspeed" value=3D"medium" checked=3D"">medium</la=
bel>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<label class=3D"radio"><input type=3D"radio" name=3D"=
flagspeed" value=3D"fast">fast</label>
        </fieldset>

    </form>

    <form autocomplete=3D"off">

        <fieldset>
            <legend>Change flags</legend>
            <label class=3D"radio"><input type=3D"radio" name=3D"flagtype" =
value=3D"O" checked=3D"">red/yellow O flags</label>&nbsp;&nbsp;<label class=
=3D"radio"><input type=3D"radio" name=3D"flagtype" value=3D"paddles">paddle=
s</label><br><label class=3D"radio"><input type=3D"radio" name=3D"flagtype"=
 value=3D"P">blue/white P flags</label><label class=3D"radio">&nbsp;&nbsp;=
=E2=80=8A<input type=3D"radio" name=3D"flagtype" value=3D"lights">lights (n=
ight)</label>
        </fieldset>

    </form>

    <form autocomplete=3D"off">

        <fieldset class=3D"wok">
            <legend>Instructions / contact</legend>

            <p></p>The exact semaphore protocol seems to vary with each ins=
titution that uses/used it (navies, armies, Boy Scouts etc.), particularly =
in the details regarding setting up the message and acknowledging it after =
sending. This software simply does an "attention" signal (also sometimes us=
ed mid-message as an error signal) at the start and end of the message. Som=
e protocols acknowledge this attention signal with a dropping of the flags =
(which can be input here with a + (plus) sign).<p></p>

            <p>Another form used for error (8 or more E signals) can be sen=
t by using ~ (tilde) as an input letter. Yet another is "annul", which can =
be input with ? (question mark).</p>

            <p>There is no such thing as case in flag semaphore: like Morse=
 code, both upper case and lower case are the same. Also note that semaphor=
e is not "handed" (i.e. it is the positions the two flags occupy which matt=
ers, <i>not which hand holds which flag</i>); skilled operators (and this s=
oftware) take the shortest combined path to flags' new positions even if th=
is means the arms cross the body.</p>

            <p>Semaphore has some signals doing double duty as both letters=
 and numerals. As stated above, this software does not need explicit use of=
 the "letters" and "numerals" precursor signals (it will put them in automa=
tically), but these flag positions can be input explicitly if needed with J=
 and # (hash), respectively. A space/rest is sometimes considered an implic=
it return to letters in semaphore protocols, so, for the sake of unambiguit=
y, this software sends a # signal before each contiguous run of numerals.</=
p>

            <p>To summarise, special characters used in this software [sign=
s/signals in square brackets are not used in this software]. Descriptions a=
re from the observer's point of view:<br><br><b>space</b> =E2=80=93 end of =
word/sentence; rest. <i>Both flags down.</i><br><b>J</b> =E2=80=93 letters =
to follow (put in automatically by this software).<br><b>#</b> =E2=80=93 nu=
merals to follow (put in automatically by this software). Unlike its partne=
r, J, this is a unique position with <i>one flag straight up and the other =
at 45=C2=B0 to the right of it.</i> [Some protocols use crossed flags above=
 the head for this purpose.]<br><b>!</b> =E2=80=93 attention; start message=
; end message; error. <i>Flags waved up and down several times.</i> [Some p=
rotocols signal end of message with "short vertical opposite-direction arcs=
 on left-hand side of body".]<br><b>+</b> =E2=80=93 acknowledge attention a=
nd go ahead (if at start. Some protocols signal an R instead); acknowledge =
end (if at end. Some protocols signal an R or C instead). <i>Flags straight=
 up and then dropped.</i><br><b>~</b> =E2=80=93 error. <i>Eight or more E l=
etters.</i> [Some protocols use a single E with circulating motion on the r=
aised flag.]<br><b>?</b> =E2=80=93 annul/cancel. <i>One flag 45=C2=B0 to th=
e left of upright, the other flag diagonally opposite.</i></p>

            <p>Email address for comments and so forth: <a>click here</a></=
p>
        </fieldset>

    </form>

   =20



